description:
Here we explore life after John Huss and Jerome. It was hoped by some that their executions would signal an end to the Reformation work in Bohemia, but this was not the case. In fact, now that John Huss was dead, his writings attracted even greater interest. The work continued and was protected during the Bohemian Hussite wars by General Jan Zizska. He never lost a battle and despite having a vastly smaller army, they were able to repel several Papal Crusades.

To find out more about the Bohemian Reformation read our extended article on their lives.
